        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Caribou ME</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Madawaska Lake, or 15 miles east of Eagle Lake, moving northeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madawaska, Madawaska Lake, Cross Lake, New Sweden, Grand Isle,
Connor, Perham, Stockholm, Westmanland, Guerette, and Cyr Plantation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
